Transcript and Presenter's Notes




Title: James Watt
 1James WattBy Kayleigh  Charlotte  2 Child HoodBorn Greenock 19th January 1736. Brother called John was shipwrecked when James was 17. Didnt go to school much but his mum taught him. When he was 18 his mum died and his dad became ill.  3 Adult Hood In 1764 married his cousin Margaret Miller had 4 children. 2 lived until toddlers. Two lived to adult hood. Margaret died in child-birth He married Anne McGregor He had 2 children who died young.   4James WattWent to London to study instrument making. Came back to Glasgow and wasnt allowed to set up his own business because he hadnt studied for 7 years. The University of Glasgow let him set up a small business in the university.   5 The Steam Engine James Watt made improvements to the steam engine. The steam engine would be very different today if James didnt improve it. We think he was a very good inventor. He also made a machine which copies things.   6IMPACT ON SOCIETYIf James hadnt improved the steam engine mines would have flooded and lots of people would of drowned.  7 DeathDied 25th of August 1819. He was 83 when he died.   8 QuizWhen was he born? How old was he when he was brother was shipwrecked? How many children altogether did he have?   9 AnswersQuestion 1- 19th January 1736 Question 2- 17 Question 3- 6 0-1 you werent listening 1-2 you need a hearing aid 3 well done you were listening well  10 Sourceswww.wikipedia.co.uk www.24hourmuseum.org.uk/trails/watt/ www.google.co.uk   11THE END 








