James Watt - Wikipedia




















 







James Watt

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

This article is about the inventor and mechanical engineer. For the college, see James Watt College. For the award, see James Watt International Medal. For other people with similar names, see James Watt (disambiguation).


James Watt



Portrait of James Watt (1736–1819)
by Carl Frederik von Breda



Born
(1736-01-19)19 January 1736
Greenock, Renfrewshire, Scotland, United Kingdom


Died
25 August 1819(1819-08-25) (aged 83)[1]
Handsworth, Birmingham, England, United Kingdom


Residence
Glasgow, Scotland, then Handsworth, England


Citizenship
